# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

Retrieves information about an existing UniFi firewall group. Lookup by either id or name.

## Example Usage

### Lookup by Name

```hcl
data "unifi_firewall_group" "blocked_ips" {
  name = "Blocked IPs"
}

output "blocked_ip_count" {
  value = length(data.unifi_firewall_group.blocked_ips.members)
}
```

### Lookup by ID

```hcl
data "unifi_firewall_group" "by_id" {
  id = "60a1b2c3d4e5f67890123456"
}
```

### Use with Firewall Rule

```hcl
data "unifi_firewall_group" "blocked_ips" {
  name = "Blocked IPs"
}

data "unifi_firewall_group" "web_ports" {
  name = "Web Ports"
}

resource "unifi_firewall_rule" "block_bad_ips" {
  name                   = "Block Bad IPs"
  action                 = "drop"
  ruleset                = "LAN_IN"
  rule_index             = 2001
  protocol               = "all"
  src_firewall_group_ids = [data.unifi_firewall_group.blocked_ips.id]
  dst_firewall_group_ids = [data.unifi_firewall_group.web_ports.id]
}
```

